      • removePrefixPath

        public Decompressor removePrefixPath(java.lang.String prefix)
                              throws java.io.IOException
        Extracts only items whose paths starts with the normalized prefix of prefix + '/'
        Paths are normalized before comparison.
        The prefix test is applied after filter(Condition) predicate is tested.
        Some entries may clash, so use overwrite(boolean) to control it.
        Some items with path that does not start from the prefix could be ignored
        Parameters:
        prefix - prefix to remove from every archive entry paths
        Returns:
        self
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
